1. Download and build Python 3.7 or the latest stable release from: https://www.python.org/downloads/source/
   Alternatively, Ubuntu users can install python 3.7
   $ sudo apt-get update
   $ sudo apt-get install python3.7
2. Download anaconda installer from: https://www.anaconda.com/products/individual
3. Follow installer prompts to install anaconda
4. Update anaconda from the terminal/command line:
   conda update conda
   conda update anaconda
5. Update scikit-learn from the terminal/command line:
   conda update scikit-learn
